3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper involves the construction of a universal cellular automaton, which may involve logical reasoning and analysis. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory): The use of signals and collisions in cellular automata may have connections to information theory and communication systems. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The construction of a smallest intrinsically universal cellular automaton may involve considerations of computational complexity.
